main event: A bright object was seen falling from the sky and landing in the Gander, Newfoundland area on February 25-26, 1958.
interesting points: A civilian reported seeing a glowing, flaming object about 5 feet in diameter that left a visible vapor trail, but no tracks, metal, or sound were found.
Radar operators at the 226th Aircraft Control and Warning Squadron detected an unidentified object on their scope, but later concluded it was likely just a bright star.
A civilian reported finding a clearing in the woods about 1/4 mile by 1000 feet, with irregularly broken and cleared trees, but no signs of heat or tracks were found.
Another civilian reported seeing a long, red streak in the sky that was likely just a snowplow clearing roads after a snowstorm.
The investigation was hampered by the unreliable reputation of one of the civilian witnesses, who was suspected of exaggerating or fabricating parts of the incident.
sighted object: a bright, glowing, flaming object about 5 feet in diameter
